<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - CRANKSHAFT
        (Reconditioning)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CRANKSHAFT (Reconditioning)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="6">
            <title>REMOVAL AND DISASSEMBLY (FOR ENGINE OVERHAUL)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the following components during engine overhaul, prior to crankshaft removal.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Remove only those components with bullet points (&#8226;) when servicing the crankshaft
                            (In chassis).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Injection Pump and Lines</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Intake Manifold</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Exhaust Manifold</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Oil Level Gauge Assembly</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Cylinder Heads</emph>
                </para>
                <para>&#8226;
                    <emph type="bold">Flywheel</emph>
                </para>
                <para>&#8226;
                    <emph type="bold">Vibration Damper</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Water Pump and Pulley</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Front Cover</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Rear Cover</emph>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">Pistons and Rods</emph>
                </para>
                <para>&#8226;
                    <emph type="bold">Oil Pan and Pump</emph>
                </para>
                <para>&#8226;
                    <emph type="bold">Glow Plugs</emph>
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4350624" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg9994" filename="../figcg9/cg9994.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.24</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350625" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10607" filename="../figcg1/cg10607.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.25</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350626" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12365a" filename="../figcg1/cg12365a.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.26</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With crankshaft pulley, damper, front cover, flywheel assembly and rear cover removed as
                    outlined earlier in this section, remove bolts from flywheel adapter and remove,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350627">6.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>In chassis crankshaft removal does not require flywheel housing removal.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Use extreme care when removing flywheel housing to prevent damaging the dowel pins.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE2295-69</emph>, damper, crankshaft and cam gear remover to remove the
                    crankshaft gear,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350628">6.28</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Attach remover plate to the crank gear using two long cap screws threaded through
                        the deep slots on the remover plate. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350628">6.28</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Be sure the large shaft protector (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350628">6.28</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ) is in place on the forcing screw.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Turn the forcing screw to remove the gear.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Crankshaft may be removed without removing the crankshaft gear.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With oil pan, oil pump and oil pickup tube assembly removed, remove the bolts from the
                    bearing caps and remove all main bearing caps,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350629">6.29</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . With bolts removed, rock the cap back and forth or tap with a plastic hammer.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The crankshaft bearing caps are numbered from the front to identify their respective
                            positions for reinstallation. The number 3 bearing cap accommodates a thrust flange to limit
                            crankshaft end play.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4350627" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12366" filename="../figcg1/cg12366.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.27</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350628" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12367" filename="../figcg1/cg12367.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.28</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350629" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11215" filename="../figcg1/cg11215.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.29</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach lifting eyes to the crankshaft and lift the crankshaft straight up and out of the
                    cylinder block,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_112.xml" xrefid="ef4350630">6.30</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the crankshaft removed, remove the upper main bearing inserts.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
